Argentine Stocks: Macro, Grupo Galicia Fall; Petrobras Rises

-- B y   L e o n   L a z a r o f f
-- 
2011-05-20T20:58:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-20/argentine-stocks-banco-macro-bbva-frances-decline-ypf-gains.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The Merval Index fell 0.1 percent to 3,383.79.  Banco Macro SA (BMA)  ,  Argentina ’s largest lender by
market value, dropped 1.7 percent to 14.70 pesos, as prices fell
for some Argentine sovereign bonds, which signals lower value
for banks’ fixed-income holdings.  BBVA Banco Frances SA (FRAN)  , the unit of  Spain ’s Banco
Bilbao Vizcaya Argentaria SA, declined 0.7 percent to 13.65
pesos.  Grupo Financiero Galicia SA (GGAL)  , Argentina’s
largest consumer lender, fell 1.4 percent to 5.49 pesos.  Petroleo Brasileiro SA (PETR4)  ,  Brazil ’s state-controlled
oil company, gained 1 percent to 74.75 pesos, as global crude
prices rose. Crude oil for June delivery gained $1.05 to settle
at $99.49 a barrel on the  New York Mercantile Exchange . Prices
fell 16 cents this week, and have risen 46 percent in the past
year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Leon Lazaroff in New York at 
